\newlabel{tab:results-sensitivity-headline}{{4.1}{40}{Single-knob sensitivity across three session sets. The user-study sessions is the cleanest benchmark: longest per-fixture rankings, zero saturated baseline divergence points. Top-$3$ and top-$5$ stability on the user-study sessions are $93.0\%$ and $98.1\%$ respectively; top-$5$ on the other two session sets is trivially $100\%$ because no fixture there has more than $5$ divergence points}{table.caption.43}{}}
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4.2}{\ignorespaces Per-knob top-$1$ disruption counts on the user-study sessions. The lag term and five of the six cleanliness sub-weights never reshuffle the highest-magnitude divergence point in the sweep; the single \texttt  {cohesion} entry reflects the lag-denominator coupling. Process-side weights account for almost every top-$1$ shift.}}{40}{table.caption.45}\protected@file@percent }
